# React UI Conventions

## Structure

- **Pages** (`src/pages/`) — route-level views: Dashboard, VariantDetail, Rules
- **Components** (`src/components/`) — reusable UI pieces
- Each component/page pairs with `*.module.css`; use CSS variables from `src/index.css`

## Patterns in this project

- Use `useProgress()` for progress state — do not prop-drill `AppState`
- Use `getVariant`, `getNextTarget` from registry for display logic
- Route params: validate with `isValidVariantId` before use; redirect invalid ids to `/`
- Mobile-first: large tap targets for "Found it!"; readable target display (mono font for targets)

## Styling

- Prefer existing CSS variables: `--color-accent`, `--color-surface`, `--color-text-muted`, etc.
- Do not introduce Tailwind or CSS-in-JS unless explicitly requested
- Empty states: show helpful hint text (see `ProgressHistory`)

## Do not

- Add backend fetch calls or auth
- Store game sequence logic in components — keep it in `src/games/`
- Import from `progressStore` in UI except for `isValidVariantId` on routes
